studyArms.name: Open-Label Run-In Arm
studyArms.description: All subjects receive open-label PF-04965842 200 mg QD for 12 weeks to identify responders.

studyArms.name: Maintenance PF-04965842
studyArms.description: Responders from the run-in period are randomized to continue PF-04965842 treatment.

studyArms.name: Maintenance Placebo
studyArms.description: Responders from the run-in period are randomized to receive matching placebo.

studyArms.name: Rescue Treatment Arm
studyArms.description: Subjects who flare during the blinded maintenance period receive open-label rescue treatment.

epochs.name: Screening
epochs.description: Up to 21 days including washout of prohibited AD treatments

epochs.name: Open-Label Run-In Period
epochs.description: 12-week induction period where all subjects receive 200 mg QD

epochs.name: Double-Blind Maintenance Treatment Period
epochs.description: Randomized withdrawal phase for responders from Week 12 to Week 52

epochs.name: Rescue Treatment Period
epochs.description: 12-week open-label treatment for subjects experiencing a flare

epochs.name: Follow-up
epochs.description: 4 weeks after the last dose of study drug
